name: Multimode_ICA_ICT_Functional
description:
Origin - QA3/VRN
  Gateway - QA1/DEN
  Destination - QA9/MSY

  NOTE: Include script to EXPECT in each screen as applicable

  Steps:
  1. Process 2 collect house air shipments from origin to destination (VRN-->MSY). Rate and bill in local currency (EUR)
  2. Process EHA shipment to INV
  3. Finish the shipments by printing on AWBPRT
  4. Confirm CFDATA is clear at Origin
  5. Attach the 2 housebills to an ICA destined to gateway (DEN)
  6. Print the MNFST
  7. Post MCTRAN
  8. Find on IC reference in CFDATA and make sure it is clear
  9. Receive ShipLog at gateway (DEN) CFIT and post the consol settlement
  10. Receive ShipLog at destination (MSY) CFIT and post the consol settlement
  11. Find on origin IC reference in gateway (DEN) DCLOG screen
  12. Enter receiving information and hit F1/Add Modify
  13. Find on IC references in gateway (DEN) CFDATA and make sure it is clear
  14. Process a prepaid truck  shipment (EHT) from gateway to final destination (DEN-->MSY). Rate and bill in local currency (USD)
  15. When processing EHT, in INV screen, enter 'N' to Post? field. Hit Add modify
  16. Go to next screen and hit Add/modify
  17. In gateway (DEN) consol, attach the original 2 HBLs (EHAs) and a new prepaid truck shipment (EHT) to an ICT destined to final destination (MSY)
  18. Print MNFST
  19. Process ICCOST, HBCOST and post MCTRAN
  20. Make sure CFDATA is clear
  21. Go back to HIST screen at the truck housebill level (EHT level)
  22. Enter 'DLV' for the Evt field. Hit Add/Modify
  23. Next, Enter 'POD' for the Evt field. Hit Add/Modify
  24. Go to INV screen at the truck housebill level (EHT level)
  25. Enter 'Y' in Post? field and hit Add/Modify
  26. Make sure CFDATA is clear
  27. Receive ShipLog at CFIT destination (MSY) and post the consol settlement


  EHA1 collect VRN - MSY (rate and bill in local currency (EUR))
  EHA2 collect VRN - MSY (rate and bill in local currency (EUR))
  ICA1 - VRN to DEN
  CFIT - POST consol settlement
  EHT3 prepaid DEN - MSY (Rate and bill in local currency (USD))
  DCT2 - DEN - MSY

name: Multimode_ICO_ICA_MCCOST
description:
Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.

  Origin - QA3/VRN
  Gateway - QA1/DEN
  Destination - QA4/YYC

  NOTE: Include script to EXPECT in each screen as applicable especially

  Create a collect EHO shipment from Origin (VRN) to Gateway (DEN). Rate and bill in foreign currency (USD)
  Process upto BLPRT and Print
  Attach the EHO to an ICO to Gateway (DEN)
  Create a collect EHA from Origin (VRN) to final Destination (YYC)
  Connect the EHA to the ICO to Gateway (DEN)
  Process the CONSOL and POST at MCTRAN
  Validate all data in MCTRAN including settling and not settling columns
  NOTE: in BLCTNR screen, need to go to Next Page and add the container number and seal number, wt, E/IO – N etc and hit Add Modify
  Click Next screen to go to CTNRDS2. Expect the 2 rows and column
  Verify CFDATA has cleared before proceeding
  Now, go to CFIT Gateway (DEN)
  Receive Shiplog – Ship Type: M
  Hit Other Keys twice to consol settlement screen
  Validate all the data for both HBs (EHO and EHA)  and update
  Validate data in consol settelment screen as well
  Post consol settlement
  Create a collect EHA shipment from gateway (DEN) to final destination (YYC). Bill and rate in foreign currency (CAD)
  Go to Export gateway (DEN) DCLOG screen
  Enter data in all applicable fields and receive the DCLOG screen
  Go to Consol and attach the 2 EHAs to ICA to final destination (YYC)
  Process CONSOL thru MCTRAN and post
  Validate all data in MCTRAN including settling and not settling columns
  Verify CFDATA has cleared before proceeding
  Now go to CFIT destination (YYC) and receive Shiplog - Ship Type: M
  Hit Other Keys twice to consol settlement screen
  Validate all the data for both HBs (EHAs) and update
  Validate data in consol settelment screen as well
  Post consol settlement

  Data:
  ------------
  EHO1 collect VRN - DEN (rate and bill in foreign currency (USD))
  EHA1 collect VRN - YYC (rate and bill in local currency (EUR))
  ICO - VRN to DEN
  Link EHO1 and EHA1 to ICO
  process and post at MCTRAN
  DEN CFIT - Post consol settlement

  EHA2 collect DEN - YYC (rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD))
  (DEN) DCLOG screen - receive consol
  ICA - DEN to YYC
  Link EHA2 to ICA
  process and post at MCTRAN
  YYC CFIT - Post consol settlement

name: Multimode_ICT_ICA_MCCOST
description:
Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.
  Transcon_IC_IC_MCTRAN one prepaid and 2 collect housebill traveling on ICT through gateway  to its final destination

  •Origin - QA1/DEN
  •Gateway - QA1/MSY
  •Destination - QA1/VRN

  NOTE:
  • While processing shipments, enter amounts into every costs field/s available (charge/rates)
  • In case of prepaid, rate and bill can be in different currencies. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill in foreign currency (INV screen)
  • In case of collect, rate and bill should be in same currency. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill should be in local currency as well (INV screen) or vice versa


  Steps:

  1. Create a prepaid EHT going from origin DEN to gateway MSY. Rate and bill in local currency (USD). Process upto AWBPRT
  2. Create a collect EHA going from origin DEN to final destination VRN. Rate and bill in foreign currency (EUR). Process upto AWBPRT
  3.Process EHT shipment to INV
  4. Create invoice that has a mix of freight revenue GL's, billing codes mapped to freight revenue and other GL's not mapped to freight revenue
  5.Finish the shipments by printing on AWBPRT
  6. Confirm CFDATA is clear at Origin
  7.Attach the housebills to an IC destined to gateway
  8.Print the MNFST
  9.Post MCTRAN
  10.Find on IC reference in CFDATA and make sure it is clear
  11.Receive ShipLog at gateway CFIT and post the consol settlement
  12.Receive ShipLog at destination CFIT and post the consol settlement
  13.Find on origin IC reference in gateway DCLOG screen
  14.Enter receiving information and hit F1/Add Modify
  15.Find on IC references in gateway CFDATA and make sure it is clear
  16.Process a collect house truck shipment from gateway to final destination. Rate and bill in foreign currency (EUR)
  17.In gateway consol, attach the original HBLs and a new collect house truck shipment to an IC destined to final destination
  18.Print MNFST
  19.Process ICCOST, HBCOST and post MCTRAN
  20.Make sure CFDATA is clear
  21.Receive ShipLog at CFIT destination and post the consol settlement


  Data:
  EHT1 – prepaid – DEN–MSY (Rate and bill in local currency (USD))
  EHA1 – collect – DEN-VRN (Rate and bill in foreign currency (EUR))
  EHT2 – collect – MSY–VRN (Rate and bill in foreign currency (EUR))
  ICT1 – DEN-MSY
  ICA2 – MSY-VRN

name: Multimode_ICT_ICO_MCCOST
description:
Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.

  Origin - QA1/DEN
  Gateway - QA9/MSY
  Destination - QA1/MIL

  NOTE: Include script to EXPECT in each screen as applicable especially
  Enter numbers in fields in all screen as applicable including HBCOST, ICCOST etc

  Create a collect EHO going from origin DEN to final destination VRN. Rate and bill in foreign currency (EUR). Process upto BLPRT and Print
  Create a prepaid EHT going from origin DEN to gateway MSY. Rate and bill in local currency (USD). Process upto AWBPRT
  Attach EHO and EHT to an ICT to gateway MSY
  Process upto MCTRAN and post
  NOTE: Perform EXPECT in all screens where possible including in MCTRAN. Important to perform EXPECT for Not Settling and Settling columns
  Validate CFDATA is clear
  Go to CFIT gateway MSY
  Validate Ship Type 'H' and Ship Type T and Ship Type 'M'
  Receive Shiplog
  Hit other keys twice to consol settlement screen
  Validate all data for both HBs (EHO and EHT) and update
  Validate data in consol settlement screen as well

  Post consol settlement
  Create a collect EHO going from gateway MSY to final destination VRN. Rate and bill in foreign currency (EUR). 
  Process upto BLPRT and Print
  Go to Export gateway MSY DCLOG screen
  Enter data in all applicable fields and recieve the DCLOG screen
  Go to Consol and attach 2 EHOs to ICO to final destination VRN
  Process CONSOL through MCTRAN and post
  Validate all data in MCTRAN including settling and not settling columns
  Verify CFDATA has cleared before proceeding
  Now go to CFIT destination (VRN) and receive Shiplog
  Hit Other Keys twice to consol settlement screen
  Validate all the data for both HBs (EHOs) and update
  Validate data in consol settelment screen as well
  Post consol settlement

  Data:
  ------------
  EHO1 collect DEN - MIL (rate and bill in foreign currency (EUR))
  EHT1 prepaid DEN - MSY (rate and bill in local currency (USD))
  ICT - DEN to MSY
  Link EHO1 and EHT1 to ICT
  process and post at MCTRAN
  MSY CFIT - Post consol settlement

  EHO2 collect MSY - MIL (rate and bill in foreign currency (EUR))
  (MSY) DCLOG screen - receive consol
  ICO - MSY to MIL
  Link EHO1 and EHO2 to ICO
  process and post at MCTRAN
  VRN CFIT - Post consol settlement
